				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Epic Question<a name="13084"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Dec 10 03 10:05 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Forpar will not speak to you until you do a favour for his friend, Vedico Windwisper, first.
<br />

<br />
Vedico is located at the Butcherblock docks in one of the shops. Upon talking to her you discover a monster stole her alluring horn and she wants it back.
<br />

<br />
You then need to head to Ocean of Tears and kill Quaq Malestrome, a cyclops. Loot the alluring horn from him and return it do Vedico, who will give you a note to Forpar.
<br />

<br />
Then head to Steamfont and play Cinda's Charismatic Carillon (alliance song) so Forpar regards you amiably. Then hand him the note from Vedico and he will speak to you.
<br />

<br />
On a side note - the old EQ Diva site has an extensive walkthrough of the epic. </span></td>
